.TH "dccp_retransmit_skb" 9 "dccp_retransmit_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dccp_retransmit_skb \- Retransmit Request, Close, or CloseReq packets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dccp_retransmit_skb
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
socket to perform retransmit on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
There are only four retransmittable packet types in DCCP:
- Request  in client-REQUEST  state (sec. 8.1.1),
- CloseReq in server-CLOSEREQ state (sec. 8.3),
- Close    in   node-CLOSING  state (sec. 8.3),
- Acks in client-PARTOPEN state (sec. 8.1.5, handled by \fBdccp_delack_timer\fP).
This function expects sk->sk_send_head to contain the original skb.
